This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation of fundus images. The use of neural networks for segmentation suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of high-resolution images and small-size lesion regions suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the mention of early diagnosis suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
